    def retranslateUi(self, topicLessonMainWindow):
        _translate = QtCore.QCoreApplication.translate
        topicLessonMainWindow.setWindowTitle(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "MainWindow"))
        self.label.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "Lessons"))
        self.label_2.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "The Conics"))
        self.label_4.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "What is Conic Section:"))
        self.label_5.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p align=\"justify\">A conic section is a special class of curves. The curves are best illustrated with the use of a plane and a two napped cone. </p><p align=\"justify\">When a plane intersects a two-napped cone, conic sections are formed. The graphic below shows how intersections of a </p><p align=\"justify\">two-napped cone and a plane form a parabola, ellipse, circle, and a hyperbola.</p></body></html>"))
        self.nextPage1Button.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "Next"))
        self.label_7.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "Circle"))
        self.label_9.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "What is a Circle"))
        self.label_10.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p align=\"justify\">A <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">circle</span> is the set of all points ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">x </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">y </span>) in a plane whose distances from a fixed point is constant. The fixed point is called </p><p align=\"justify\">the <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">center</span><span style=\" color:#000000;\"> of the circle and the constant is called the </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">radius</span><span style=\" color:#000000;\"> of the circle.</span></p></body></html>"))
        self.label_12.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p><span style=\" font-size:20pt;\">Standard Equation of Circle</span></p><p>The standard equation of a circle with center at ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) and radius of length r &gt; 0 is. </p></body></html>"))
        self.label_14.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>The \'<span style=\" font-style:italic;\">h </span>\' and the \'<span style=\" font-style:italic;\">k </span>\' relate to the center of the circle ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) and the \'r\' stands for the <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">radius</span> of the circle. </p><p>The radius is defined as the distance from the center to all points on the circle</p></body></html>"))
        self.label_15.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "Completing the Square"))
        self.label_16.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>In general, any equation of the form </p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">A</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + A</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + B</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + C</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + D = 0</span><br/></p><p>will produce a circle. Notice that the square terms have matching coefficients. If the squared terms have different </p><p>coefficients, the graph won\'t be a circle. thus it will be an ellipse. An ellipse has an oval shape.</p><p><br/></p><p>We can use a technique called <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">completing the square</span> to rewrite such an equation so that we can quickly identify </p><p>the circle\'s center point ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> ) and the radius.</p></body></html>"))
        self.label_18.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>Example:</p><p>Find the center and the radius of a circle having the equation:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + 2x - 6y + 1 = 0</span></p><p>Solution:</p><p>- Group the <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">x</span>\'s and <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">y</span>\'s together:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#000000;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> ) + ( y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">6</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#000000;\">y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> ) + 1 = 0</span></p><p align=\"center\"><br/></p><p>- Divide the linear term coefficients ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">2</span> and <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">6 </span>) by 2 and squaring it:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> / 2 = 1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#ffffff;\">qqqqqqqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">6 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">/ 2 = 3</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#ffffff;\">qqqqqqqqqqqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">3</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">9</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + 2x + </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> ) + ( y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - 6y + </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">9</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> ) = - 1 + </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">9</span></p><p align=\"center\"><br/></p><p>- Use <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">Perfect square Factorization</span>, when an expression has the general form <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">a</span><span style=\" font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" color:#00da00;\">+ </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">2ab</span><span style=\" color:#00da00;\"> + </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">b</span><span style=\" font-weight:600; font-style:italic; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span>we can factor it as <span style=\" color:#00da00;\">( </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">a</span><span style=\" color:#00da00;\"> + </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">b</span><span style=\" color:#00da00;\"> )</span><span style=\" font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span>, </p><p>thus when an expression has the general form <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">a</span><span style=\" font-weight:600; color:#0000ff; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span><span style=\" color:#0000ff;\">- </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">2ab</span><span style=\" color:#0000ff;\"> + </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">b</span><span style=\" font-weight:600; font-style:italic; color:#0000ff; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span>we can factor it as <span style=\" color:#0000ff;\">( </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">a</span><span style=\" color:#0000ff;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">b</span><span style=\" color:#0000ff;\"> )</span><span style=\" font-weight:600; color:#0000ff; vertical-align:super;\">2</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">( x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\"> + 2x + 1 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">( x + 1 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">( y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#0000ff; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\"> - 6y + 9 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">( y - 3 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#0000ff; vertical-align:super;\">2</span></p><p align=\"center\"><br/></p><p>- The equation will become :</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( x + 1 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">+ ( y - 3 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= 3</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; vertical-align:super;\">2</span></p><p><br/></p><p>- To show the center of the circle and the radius we need to, remove the <span style=\" color:#00da00;\">squares</span> ( <span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( x + 1 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">+ ( y - 3 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= 3</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">) </span></p><p>we can put square root to the squared binomials and the squared constant.</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( x + 1 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= 0</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( y - 3 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= 0</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">3</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#00da00; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><br/></p><p>- this removes the squared and remains the coefficients and variables, with the squared in the </p><p>constant, it can be leave as it is if it cannot be square rooted to.</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">x + 1 = 0</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">y - 3 = 0</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">3</span><br/></p><p>- This shows that the center of the circle and the radius of the circle is:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">x = -1 y = 3 r = 3</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( -1 , 3 ) r = 3</span><br/></p></body></html>"))
