        self.label_24.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p align=\"justify\">A <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">parabola</span> is the set of all points ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">x </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">y </span>) in a plane that are equidistant from a fixed line, called the <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">directrix</span>, and a </p><p align=\"justify\">fixed point called the <span style=\" text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">focus</span>, not on the line. The <span style=\" text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">vertex</span> is the midpoint between the focus and the directrix.</p><p align=\"justify\">The <span style=\" text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">axis of symmetry</span> of the parabola is the line passing through the focus and the vertex. </p></body></html>"))
        self.label_26.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p><span style=\" font-size:20pt;\">Standard Equation of Parabola</span></p><p>The standard equation of a parabola with vertex at ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) is ( <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">Note</span>: != is not equal ):</p><p>1. ( <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">x</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> = 4<span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p ( y</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>), <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p</span> != 0 when the directrix is <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">y </span>= <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p </span>so that the axis is vertical</p><p>2. ( y - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> = 4<span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p ( x</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span>), <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p</span> != 0 when the directrix is <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">x </span>= <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p </span>so that the axis is horizontal<br/></p></body></html>"))
        self.label_28.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>If the equation of a parabola is ( <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">x</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> = 4<span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p ( y</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>)</p><p>the vertex is the point ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) the focus is ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>+ <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p</span> ).</p><p>The parabola opens upward if <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p</span> &gt; 0 and opens downward if <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p </span>&lt; 0.<br/></p></body></html>"))
        self.label_29.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>Example:</p><p>Find the equation of the parabola with <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">vertex</span> at ( 0 , 0 ) and <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">focus</span> at ( 0 , -5 ).</p><p>- Plot the points on a rectangular coordinate system.</p></body></html>"))
        self.parabolaEx1PlotButton.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "Show the Graph"))
        self.label_31.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>The focus ( 0 , 5 ) is below the vertex ( 0 , 0 ), the parabola opens downard. </p><p>This shows the equation of the parabola as:<br/></p><p>Solution:</p><p>- A parabola that opens downward has an equation ( <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">x</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> = 4<span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p ( y</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) with vertex ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> , <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> ) and focus at ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> , <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> + p ). </p><p>This shows that the vertex ( 0 , 0 ) gives <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> = 0 and <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> = 0. The focus is ( 0 , -5 ) this implies that the focus is 5 units </p><p>below the vertex which gives us p = -5. </p><p>The equation of the parabola is:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 4</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">p ( y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">)</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">0</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 4( -5 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">( y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">0 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">)</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = -20</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic;\">y</span><br/></p></body></html>"))
        self.label_27.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>If the equation of a parabola is ( y - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> = 4<span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p ( x</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span>)</p><p>the vertex is the point ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) the focus is ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>+ <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p</span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>).</p><p>The parabola opens to the right if <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p</span> &gt; 0 and opens to the left if <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p </span>&lt; 0.</p></body></html>"))
        self.label_32.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>Example:</p><p>Reduce the equation of the parabola y<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> - 6y - 8x + 1 = 0 to standard form:</p><p>Solution:</p><p>- Rearrange the equation so that the second-degree term and the first-degree term of </p><p>the same variable are on the left side and place the rest on the right:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - 6y = 8x - 1</span></p><p>- Use complete the square in y:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> - 6y + 9 = 8x - 1 + 9</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( y - 3 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 8x - 8</span></p><p align=\"center\"><br/></p><p><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">- </span>Rewrite the equation to standard form ( y - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span>= 4p ( x - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> ):</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( y - 3 )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 8x - 8</span></p><p align=\"center\"><br/></p><p>- We can factor out 8 in the right side of the equation:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( y - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">3</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> )</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> = 8 ( x + </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> )</span></p><p>- The <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">vertex</span> of the parabola based from ( y - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span>= 4p ( x - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> ) is:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">-1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> , </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">3</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> ) </span></p><p>- The <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#ff0000;\">p</span> of the parabola based from ( y - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k</span> )<span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2 </span>= 4p ( x - <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> ) is:</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">8 = 4p</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">8 / 4 = 4p / 4</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">p = 2</span></p><p>- The <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">focus</span> of the parabola, remember that focus is ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>+ <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">p</span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>):</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#00da00;\">-1</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\"> + 2, </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#0000ff;\">3 </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">)</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">( 1 , 3 )</span><br/></p></body></html>"))
