        self.label_38.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p align=\"justify\">An <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">ellipse</span> is the set of all points ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">x </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">y </span>) in a plane in which the sum of whose distances from two distinct fixed points, </p><p align=\"justify\">called <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">foci</span> is constant.<br/></p><p align=\"justify\">The line through the foci intersects the ellipse at two points called <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#ff0000;\">vertices</span>. The chord joining the vertices is the </p><p align=\"justify\"><span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#ff0000;\">major axis</span> and its midpoint is the <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#ff0000;\">center</span> of the ellipse. The chord perpendicular to the major axis at the center </p><p align=\"justify\">is the <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#ff0000;\">minor axis</span> of the ellipse.</p></body></html>"))
        self.label_40.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p><span style=\" font-size:20pt;\">Standard Equation of Ellipse</span></p><p>The standard equation of an ellipse with center at ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) and major and minor axes of lengths 2a and 2b, </p><p>respectively, where a &gt; b &gt; 0, is ( <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">Note:</span> != is not equal ):</p><p>1. <span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\">( </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">x</span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#00da00;\">h </span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">+ </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">( y</span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#0000ff;\">k </span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= </span>1, when the major axis is horizontal.</p><p><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#ffffff;\">qqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">a</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#ffffff; vertical-align:super;\">qqqqqqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">b</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span></p><p>2. <span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\">( </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">x</span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#00da00;\">h </span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">+ </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">( y</span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#0000ff;\">k </span><span style=\" text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= </span>1, when the major axis is vertical. </p><p><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#ffffff;\">qqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">b</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#ffffff; vertical-align:super;\">qqqqqqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">a</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span></p><p>The <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">foci</span> is in the major axis, <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">c</span> units from the <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">center</span> where <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">c</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; font-style:italic; vertical-align:super;\">2</span>= <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">a</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; font-style:italic; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">b</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; font-style:italic; vertical-align:super;\">2</span>.</p></body></html>"))
        self.label_41.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p><br/></p></body></html>"))
        self.label_42.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>If the equation of the ellipse is the form ( <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">Note</span>: +/- means plus or minus, positive or negative )</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\">( </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#00da00;\">h</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">+ </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">( y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#0000ff;\">k</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= 1</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#ffffff;\">qa</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">a</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#ffffff; vertical-align:super;\">qqqaaaqqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">b</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#ffffff; vertical-align:super;\">qqaqaq</span></p><p>The center is ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> , <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) and its major axis is parallel to the <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">x-axis</span>. </p><p>The vertices are located ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> +/- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">a </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>)</p><p>The foci are the points ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> +/- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">c </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>)</p><p>The Endpoints of its minor axis are ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>+/- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">b </span>) <br/><br/></p><p>If the equation of the ellipse is the form ( <span style=\" color:#ff0000;\">Note</span>: +/- means plus or minus, positive or negative )</p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\">( </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">x</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#00da00;\">h</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">+ </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline;\">( y</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\"> - </span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#0000ff;\">k</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; text-decoration: underline;\">)</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">= 1</span></p><p align=\"center\"><span style=\" font-size:18pt; color:#ffffff;\">a</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">b</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#ffffff; vertical-align:super;\">qqqqqqqq</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt;\">a</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; color:#ffffff; vertical-align:super;\">aaaaa</span></p><p>The center is ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h</span> , <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) and its major axis is parallel to the <span style=\" font-style:italic; text-decoration: underline; color:#ff0000;\">y-axis</span>. </p><p>The vertices are located ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>+/- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">a </span>)</p><p>The foci are the points ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>+/- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">c </span>)</p><p>The Endpoints of its minor axis are ( <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#00da00;\">h </span>+/- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">b </span>, <span style=\" font-style:italic; color:#0000ff;\">k </span>) <br/></p></body></html>"))
        self.label_50.setText(_translate("topicLessonMainWindow", "<html><head/><body><p>Additional Info:</p><p>- The center ,foci and the vertices are all on the major axis.</p><p>- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">a</span> is the distance from the center to each vertex. <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">c</span> is the distance from the center </p><p>to each focus. <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">b</span> is the distance from tehcenter to an endpoint of the minor axis. </p><p>- <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">a</span> &gt; <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">b</span> and <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">c</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> = <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">a</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span> - <span style=\" font-style:italic;\">b</span><span style=\" font-size:18pt; font-weight:600; vertical-align:super;\">2</span>.</p></body></html>"))
